Name: test command
Documentation:
• Object invariants are conditions that should be true for each instance of a class whenever that object is visible to a client. They express the conditions under which the object is considered to be correct.
• During run-time checking, invariants are checked at the end of each public method.

Name: Conditions that must be met, so that the post-condition gives a guaranteed result
The side effects of the operation are the guaranteed consequences of calling the method
